name: Go workshop
description:
Go is a small language, but one with a few differences to many common languages. For example, Go supports an Object Oriented style of development, but doesn't have classes, and it has built-in primitives to simplify concurrent programming.

This workshop is aimed at introducing these concepts to someone new to Go, but not new to programming in general. 

Feel welcome to drop by on March 24th at Devhouse Spindle, located in The Big Building. We’ll start at 7:30 PM and of course there will be drinks and snacks to keep you concentrated ;) Hope to see you there!
